rComments: Great prof. He always made everything clear and related course material to real applications (something that is surprisingly rare at U of T's APPLIED science department). He also did a 10min review of the previous lecture at the beginning of each lecture so people weren't completely lost if they were half asleep during the last session.

Do past exams and midterms. The content is quite similar. I mostly asked TA's for help, instead of office hours. Tutorials are helpful. Most of the course is simple math, and some memorization. It was a more relaxed course.

This guy is the worst professor in the history of UofT. The final exam was very inconsistent with the material taught. His teaching style is not a style, but a liability on students. He made an interesting course a boring one. I recommend not taking a course under him.

I can't stand this guy.  He turns an interesting and straight forward course into a complicated messed up one.  His problem sets are not a good indiciation of what to expect on the midterm since he makes something that was covered for 2 minutes in class to be half the exam.  Two thumbs down.
